<br>
Here are some facts:<br>
<br>
*If you make threads criticizing people for correcting other people's grammar and generally expecting at least a 6th-grade writing level to be present in a text-based communications medium, you're an idiot.<br>
<br>
*If your primary means of communication in a given situation is the written word, and you fail to put forth even the most cursory effort to make your writing appear to be well-constructed and coherent, you're an idiot, and will be judged by your peers as such.<br>
<br>
*If you revel in your ignorance, and angrily lash out against anyone who calls you an ignoramus, you're an idiot.<br>
<br>
*If you blame the public school system, your parents, society-at-large, God, the military industrial complex, etc. etc. ad infinitum for your own laziness and utter lack of motivation to learn the language into which you were born, you're not only an idiot, you're also lazy and you subscribe to a victim mentality.<br>
<br>
*If you're trying to out-rant someone, the effect of your caustic barbs and petty insults will be decreased exponentially for every spelling or grammatical error present in your rant.  Ultimately this will probably serve to prove correct whatever opinion the person you're trying to rant expressed about you in the first place.<br>
<br>
*If you find yourself constantly trying to justify your intelligence level with ridiculous proclamations like &quot;just because I don't tyep good Englsih doesnt mean Im not smart,&quot; you're an idiot, and you're every bit as dumb as you've been accused of being--you're also delusional.<br>
<br>
*Lastly, and most importantly:  the inability to competently write or speak the English language is nothing to be ashamed of, IF you're mature enough to realize your limitations and strive to improve your ability.  True students NEVER stop learning, and never completely rule someone else's opinions out--the willingness to better yourself, coupled with the maturity to recognize your own flaws and strive to constantly improve yourself are the marks of a truly intelligent person.  <br>
<br>
So the next time someone corrects your grammar, maybe you should consider taking their criticism to heart and LEARNING.  Otherwise, you're an idiot.<br>
<br>
